  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "GRxL1QXEUbS9bEyxclCLlDKm+G0=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:36.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Model\n\nLive collaboration on a drive or document is **multi-writer**: each collaborator writes their own ops to their own feed, and everyone reads everyone else's. ACT gates read access (drive-level first, narrowed to doc-level later).\n\n## Flow\n\n1. Each peer mines a GSOC signer for the other's overlay (one-time, ~10\u201330s).\n2. Signers are exchanged via PSS (trusted channel, one-to-one).\n3. On op-committed, SwarmChannel pushes the op batch to the author's feed and sends a GSOC `doc-updated` ping to each other collaborator.\n4. Receivers pull new batches from the author's feed via `reactor.load()`.\n5. A timer-based poll remains as fallback when GSOC pings are missed.\n\n## GSOC notification payload\n\n```typescript\n{\n  type: \"doc-updated\",\n  documentId: \"b9e4fe2e-...\",\n  driveId: \"96ffdf26-...\",\n  fromAddress: \"0xadbA7C2F...\",\n  latestIndex: { document: 5, global: 12 },\n  timestamp: \"2026-04-15T18:30:05Z\"\n}\n```\n\nThe payload is small (<4KB) and only tells the receiver's SwarmChannel to pull; the actual ops travel via the feed.\n\n## Debouncing\n\nGSOC-triggered pulls are debounced so a flurry of ops (e.g. rapid typing) coalesces into a single pull.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:36.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:36.000Z"
    }
  },
